					<li class="book-item"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20211027040424/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/Mal">Malachias</a></li>
					<li class="book-item"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20211027040424/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Mac">1 Machabees</a></li>
					<li class="book-item"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20211027040424/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/2_Mac">2 Machabees</a></li>
			</ul>
</div>
	<div class="main">
		<div class="main-content">
			<div class="book-header">
				<div class="vers-view-type">
					<a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20211027040424/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/Esd/7249?vers_inline=1"><img src="https://web.archive.org/web/20211027040424im_/http://catholicbible.online/assets/img/para.jpg" alt=""/></a>					<a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20211027040424/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/Esd/7249?comments_open=1"><img src="https://web.archive.org/web/20211027040424im_/http://catholicbible.online/assets/img/C-off.gif" alt=""/></a>				</div>
				<div class="bible-name">The Holy Bible – Knox Translation</div>
				<div class="book-name">The First Book of Esdras </div>
				<div class="act-chapter">
					<div class="prev-chapter"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20211027040424/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/Esd/7248">&lt; prev</a></div>|
					<div class="chapter">Chapter 8</div>
					|<div class="next-chapter"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20211027040424/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/Esd/7250">next &gt;</a></div>
				</div>
				<div class="chapters">
					<a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20211027040424/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/Esd/ch_1">1</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20211027040424/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/Esd/ch_2">2</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20211027040424/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/Esd/ch_3">3</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20211027040424/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/Esd/ch_4">4</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20211027040424/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/Esd/ch_5">5</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20211027040424/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/Esd/ch_6">6</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20211027040424/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/Esd/ch_7">7</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20211027040424/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/Esd/ch_8" class="active">8</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20211027040424/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/Esd/ch_9">9</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20211027040424/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/Esd/ch_10">10</a> 				</div>
			</div>
						<div class="verses">
									<div id="vers156598" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">1</div>
						<div class="vers-content">The leaders, who took part with me in this migration under Artaxerxes, were descended as follows:</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156599" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">2</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Gersom was of the stock of Phinees, Daniel of Ithamar, Hattus of David.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156600" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">3</div>
						<div class="vers-content">These were the numbers the various clans provided: Pharos (of the sons of Sechenias), a hundred and fifty under Zacharias;</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156601" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">4</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Phahath-Moab, two hundred under Elioenai, son of Zarehe;</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156602" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">5</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Sechenias, three hundred under …, son of Ezechiel;</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156603" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">6</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Adan, fifty under Abed son of Jonathan;</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156604" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">7</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Alam, seventy under Isaias son of Athalias;</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156605" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">8</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Saphatia, eighty under Zebedia son of Michael;</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156606" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">9</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Joab, two hundred and eighteen under Obedia son of Jahiel;</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156607" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">10</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Selomith, a hundred and sixty under …, son of Josphia;</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156608" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">11</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Bebai, twenty-eight under Bebai’s son Zacharias;</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156609" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">12</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Azgad, a hundred and ten under Johanan son of Eccetan;</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156610" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">13</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Adonicam, sixty, under his last remaining sons, Elipheleth, Jehiel and Samaias;</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156611" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">14</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Begui, seventy under Uthai and Zachur.<span class="content-paragraph"><br><br></span></div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156612" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">15</div>
						<div class="vers-content">We made a halt of three days by the Ahava river; and there I found that I had common folk with me and priests, but no Levites.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156613" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">16</div>
						<div class="vers-content">So I despatched some of the chiefs, Eliezer, Ariel, Semeias, Elnathan, Jarib, (a second Elnathan,) Nathan, Zacharias and Mosollam, with two prudent counsellors, Joiarib and Elnathan,</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156614" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">17</div>
						<div class="vers-content">to Eddo, who was in command at Casphia; I bade them ask Eddo and the Nathinaeans who were there with him to supply us with ministers for the house of our God.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156615" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">18</div>
						<div class="vers-content">And they, by God’s favour, sent us …, a Levite of Moholi’s clan, with Sarabias and eighteen more of his kinsmen;</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156616" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">19</div>
						<div class="vers-content">also a Merarite, Hasabias, with Isaias and twenty more of his.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156617" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">20</div>
						<div class="vers-content">There were also two hundred and twenty Nathinaeans; these Nathinaeans were men bound over by David and David’s councillors to the service of the Levites. A list of all their names was supplied to us.<a href="" class="inline-comment" data-comment-id="697">✻</a> <span class="content-paragraph"><br><br></span></div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156618" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">21</div>
						<div class="vers-content">There, by the Ahava river, I proclaimed a fast; we would do penance, and ask of the Lord our God a safe journey for ourselves, for the children who went with us, and for all that was ours.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156619" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">22</div>
						<div class="vers-content">I would have asked the king for an escort of horsemen to defend us from attack, but shame withheld me; had we not boasted in the king’s presence that our God graciously protected all who had recourse to him, that only faithless servants of his brought down on themselves the constraining power of his vengeance?</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156620" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">23</div>
						<div class="vers-content">So fast we did, to win the favour we asked of God, and all went well.<span class="content-paragraph"><br><br></span></div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156621" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">24</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Then I chose twelve of the leading priests, Sarabias and Hasabias with ten others,</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156622" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">25</div>
						<div class="vers-content">and handed over to them the offerings made by king, councillors, and nobles, and by such Israelites as came forward with gifts; the whole weight of silver and gold, and all the hallowed appurtenances of our God’s temple.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156623" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">26</div>
						<div class="vers-content">It was six hundred and fifty talents of silver I paid over to them, with a hundred pieces of silver ware; and a hundred talents of gold,</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156624" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">27</div>
						<div class="vers-content">with twelve bowls of the same metal, each of ten pounds’ weight, and two pieces of the finest bronze ware, like gold itself for beauty.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156625" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">28</div>
						<div class="vers-content">You are consecrated to the Lord, I told them, and here are consecrated things; here are silver and gold offered as a free gift to the Lord God of our fathers.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156626" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">29</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Keep watchful guard over them; you are answerable for delivering them safely, in the presence of priest and Levite and clan chief there in Jerusalem, into the treasury of our God.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156627" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">30</div>
						<div class="vers-content">So these priests and Levites took all that weight of silver and gold into their keeping, and the ornaments besides, that must be brought safely to the house of our God at Jerusalem.<span class="content-paragraph"><br><br></span></div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156628" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">31</div>
						<div class="vers-content">We left the Ahava river on the twelfth day of the first month, bound for Jerusalem; and, with our God protecting us from all peril on the way, of open enemy or secret,</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156629" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">32</div>
						<div class="vers-content">to Jerusalem we came. We had been there but three days</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156630" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">33</div>
						<div class="vers-content">before silver, gold and ornaments, were delivered safe in our God’s temple. Meremoth, son of the priest Urias, and Eleazar, son of Phinees, with two Levites, Jozabed son of Josue and Noadaia son of Bennoi,</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156631" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">34</div>
						<div class="vers-content">handed it over, all counted and weighed, and its weight was duly entered.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156632" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">35</div>
						<div class="vers-content">And these exiles, restored now from captivity, offered the God of Israel burnt-sacrifice; twelve calves for the twelve tribes of Israel, ninety rams and seventy-seven lambs, besides twelve goats as an offering for fault. Such was the burnt-sacrifice they made in the Lord’s honour;</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers156633" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">36</div>
						<div class="vers-content">then they delivered the royal edict to the governors, that were the king’s officers; and now God’s people and God’s house were held in honour by all that bore rule in the country west of Euphrates.<span class="content-paragraph"><br><br></span></div>
					</div>
							</div>
			<div class="book-footer">
				<div class="act-chapter">
